(nICacheWays, power_leakage).explanation: Increasing the number of instruction cache ways requires additional transistors and memory cells, which directly increases static power consumption through leakage currents;

(nICacheWays, area_cell_area).explanation: More instruction cache ways necessitate additional memory cells and associated circuitry, directly increasing the total cell area on the chip;

(nICacheWays, nDCacheMSHRs).explanation: The number of instruction cache ways and data cache miss status holding registers are independent design parameters that serve different functions in the memory hierarchy;
